quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  106,1,The union of the people of Qoraish into one whole body
  106,2,And the safety of their customary trade journeys winter and summer
  106,3,"Are owed to Allah, the Sovereign of this Sanctuary -AL-Kaâ€™ba- Whom they should worship, and Him alone they should adore"
  106,4,He saved them from hunger and gave them the security they longed for
  107,1,Do you see the one who denies religion and does not recognize Allah nor His control and government of all events
  107,2,Such is he who ill-treats the orphan
  107,3,And discourages aid to the indigent faint soul past corporal toil
  107,4,"And so, Woe to those who make great pretences to religion and their hearts' ears to exhortation are not inclined"
  107,5,"Who are oblivious of their act of worship, and when they perform it, their countenances reflect and speak absence of mind"
  107,6,"Who cultivate pretence and they, themselves, are empty of all good"
  107,7,Their malevolence prevents benevolence and proves an occasion of so much discontent
  108,1,"We have bestowed on you O Muhammad AL-Kawther which is the abundance of good things. We favoured you with a good many blessings of magnificence and imposing magnitude here and Hereafter including knowledge, wisdom, distinction, followers, immunity, fame and insight"
  108,2,"In return, perform your prayer first, then execute the sacrifice whose meat you distribute among the needy till benevolence has had its rite"
  108,3,As to your enemy who bore malice to you; it is he and not you who shall he cut off all hope and posterity and drown in shame. He will be denied the praise of his name to fame